Job Description:
Arup is the creative force at the heart of many of the world’s most prominent projects in the built environment and across industry. Working in more than 140 countries, the firm’s designers, engineers, architects, planners, consultants and technical specialists work with our clients on innovative projects of the highest quality and impact. We embrace equality, diversity and inclusion in all aspects including individual differences and open-mindedness

Responsibilities:
• Undertake design of plumbing & fire protection system for a variety of projects (primary focus on Data Centre, residential, office, with future development in Transport infrastructure).
• Most of the work will be as part of multidisciplinary project in collaboration with other disciplines in the office (particularly the Structures team).
• The project may be located in Vietnam or elsewhere.
Role
• Serve as Plumbing Engineer;
• Directly involved in the preparation of study reports, design reports and technical notes;
• Directly involved in the preparation of technical documentation from Concept through to Construction Stages – work may involve analysis, calculation, design, and preliminary preparation of BIM model (for further development by dedicated BIM teams);
• Directly involved in preparing and reviewing specifications, responding to client and contractor requests as may be required;
• Will be responsible for the design of Plumbing & Fire Protection systems for a wide range of projects, including Data Centre, commercial, residential, industrial and healthcare.

Job Requirements:
• 0 to 5 years relevant working experience;
• From an Plumbing/Fire Protection background (as appropriate);
• Bachelor degree in in Plumbing/Fire Protection Engineering, as appropriate;
• Fluency in English (spoken & written) is advantageous; if not, continued development in English will be expected upon joining;
• Experience in REVIT and Navisworks is advantageous however training can be provided;

Job Description:
Arup is the creative force at the heart of many of the world’s most prominent projects in the built environment and across industry. Working in more than 140 countries, the firm’s designers, engineers, architects, planners, consultants and technical specialists work with our clients on innovative projects of the highest quality and impact. We embrace equality, diversity and inclusion in all aspects including individual differences and open-mindedness..

Responsibilities:
